---
description: Shared project memory, local-first Git workflow, and safe remote execution rules
alwaysApply: true
---

Before changing project files, read `PROJECT_INDEX.md` and `AGENTS.md`.

Treat the local checkout as the only development, editing, testing, commit, and
push path. Treat the SSH server as the runtime and large-result storage path.

Before any remote commit/push/submission, present the review package and wait for
explicit user approval. For Slurm work, read the relevant protocol under
`docs/codex/` and verify the smoke-test `.out` and `.err` requirements.

Do not silently delete, overwrite, or download raw data or large intermediates.
